The paper deals with computational complexity of computing voting power indices in a coalitional game, which is a topic in computational game theory (cs.GT). The game considered is based on a graph, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of graph theory (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms and complexity for computing these indices, which could fall under the sub-category of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of these indices in artificial intelligence applications, which could place it under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with connectivity and network flow games, which could suggest the sub-category of computer networks and communications (cs.CC).
